node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

node.title: A Safe Haven for Frontline Workers - Four Seasons Hotel New York

Rain or shine, @antonio.pozo's spirits can't be dampened—especially in the Maldives! 😎🙌🏼 While most pictures and videos show you its impeccably warm weather, the Maldives also experiences torrential rain usually around mid-May to November. 🌧

This was taken in the Baa Atoll, which consists of three separate natural atolls, namely southern Maalhosmadulu Atoll, the Fasdūtherē Atoll, and Goifulhafehendhu Atoll. It's a UNESCO-designated Biosphere Reserve, drawing in snorkelers and divers all year round. 🇲🇻

Wherever you are in the world: what season is it there, and how's the weather like where you are? 💭

📽️ @antonio.pozo
📍 Baa Atoll, Maldives
🎶 Danheim - Kala

Tag a homebody and see what they think about this! 😂

Relishing in @schnapsandschnitzel's view of the breathtaking Gosau Lake. 😍 Embedded in natural surroundings, the Gosau Lake is a small mountain lake surrounded by the Dachstein Mountains. ⛰

Not only is the place famous for its unparalleled natural beauty, but because of its clear and pristine water that's suitable for drinking. With its unique scenery, it's a sought-after place in Austria for an unforgettable day trip. 💧

Have you been here? What are other unmissable spots to visit in Austria? 🇦🇹

📍 Gosau Lake, Austria

Let @ryanresatka show you the most incredible pool with a view amidst the Swiss Alps. It really doesn't get better than this, don't you think? 🤩

This was shot in the municipality of Ennetbürgen in the canton of Nidwalden in Switzerland. With a 34ºC heated outdoor pool, views of Lake Lucerne, and space for quiet and contemplation, this is just one among the many gems of Switzerland that makes you fall in love with the country. 🇨🇭

Can you guess the name of this popular stay and does this make you want to travel to Switzerland in the future? ❤️

📽 @ryanresatka 
📍 Switzerland
🎶 Powfu, beabadoobee - death bed (coffee for your head)

Dining in style with @voyage_provocateur in none other than Paris. ✨ There are many unmissable places to see and experience in this city, but this majestic restaurant is surely at the top of that list! 🍷

Located at Gare de Lyon, Le Train Bleu is an iconic gourmet restaurant known for its exceptional cuisine and design. Sophisticated yet cozy, it's more than a stopover for curious travelers, offering the most memorable setting for timeless memories. If you want to discover more must-visit restaurants, check out @beautifulcuisines. 😉

What are your favorite restaurants in Paris? 🇫🇷
